author: wtopstaff
title: Ole Miss’ Nkemdiche leaves game, has possible head injury
text:
By The Associated Press October 17, 2015 1:36 pm 
MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) — Mississippi’s Robert Nkemdiche left Saturday’s game against Memphis in the second quarter because of a possible head injury. 
Ole Miss said Nkemdiche’s return was questionable. 
The 6-foot-5, 296-pound Nkemdiche, who usually plays defensive tackle, was injured while running the ball in a short-yardage situation. He’s been used several times on offense this season and scored three touchdowns.
